{"cursor":"4580","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox person\n| name = Takeshi Obata image = alt = caption = birth_date = birth_place =\n| Niigata, Niigata Prefecture, Japan death_date =  death_place = nationality = Japanese other_names = known_for =\n| occupation = Manga artist, Game artist, Artist, Illustrator, Penciller, Inker\n}} is a Japanese manga artist. He works as the artist in collaboration with a\nwriter. He has also mentored several manga artists, including Kentaro Yabuki of\n[[Black Cat (manga)|Black Cat]] fame, Nobuhiro Watsuki of [[Rurouni Kenshin]]\nand [[Busou Renkin]], and Yusuke Murata of [[Eyeshield 21]].\n\nHe originally became noticed in 1985 when he took a prize in the Tezuka Award\nfor his one shot 500 KÅnen no shinwa. Joining the\n[[Weekly Shonen Jump]] staff, he mentored under Makoto Niwano before starting\nhis first major series, writing and drawing Cyborg Jii-chan G in 1989. Having\ndifficulty for several years in finding a hit, Obata began collaborating with\nother writers on their stories. He finally began the series that established his\nname when he teamed with Yumi Hotta on [[Hikaru no Go]] starting in 1998.\n\nHe is most well known as the artist of [[Hikaru no Go]], for which he received\nthe Shogakukan Manga Award in 2000 and the\nTezuka Osamu Cultural Prize in 2003, and [[Death Note]]. Obata is rare among\nshÅnen artists not only for the detail of his drawings, but in his penchant for\nfashion; the characters he draws often wear stylish clothes and trendy items\nlike the latest fashionable scarf, tie or handbag.\n\nHe has served as the artist of [[Blue Dragon Ral Grad]], a manga adaptation of\nthe fantasy video game,[[Blue Dragon]] from December 2006 to July 2007.\n\nIn the fall of 2007, he drew a short story, Hello Baby, with writer Masanori\nMorita, which appeared in [[Jump\nSquare]]. [http://jumpsq.shueisha.co.jp/contents/yomikiri/index.html]\nThis was followed by a one-shot manga with Nisio Isin. He has recently completed\nhis latest series with Tsugumi Ohba, [[Bakuman]], which ran from August 2008 to\nApril 2012.\n\nIn addition to his manga work, he has also done character design work for\nthe video game [[Castlevania Judgment]], as well as illustrating several\nlight novels.\n","linknr":276,"url":"Takeshi_Obata","recorded":1375068704,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Takeshi_Obata&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Takeshi_Obata&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Niigata,_Niigata","/wiki/Niigata_Prefecture","/wiki/Mangaka","/wiki/Game_artist","/wiki/Artist","/wiki/Illustrator","/wiki/Penciller","/wiki/Inker","/wiki/Help:Installing_Japanese_character_sets","/wiki/Mangaka","/wiki/Kentaro_Yabuki","/wiki/Black_Cat_(manga)","/wiki/Nobuhiro_Watsuki","/wiki/Rurouni_Kenshin","/wiki/Busou_Renkin","/wiki/Yusuke_Murata","/wiki/Eyeshield_21","/wiki/Tezuka_Award","#cite_note-TezukaAward-1","/wiki/Weekly_Shonen_Jump","/wiki/Makoto_Niwano","/wiki/Yumi_Hotta","/wiki/Hikaru_no_Go","/wiki/Hikaru_no_Go","/wiki/Shogakukan_Manga_Award","#cite_note-ShogakukanAward-2","/wiki/Tezuka_Osamu_Cultural_Prize","/wiki/Death_Note","/wiki/Sh%C5%8Dnen","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed","/wiki/Blue_Dragon_Ral_Grad","/wiki/Blu